OL,3,C'Lives could be lost' due to Llanelli
OL,4,Cminor injuries unit cuts, campaigners
OL,5,Csay
OL,7,FAround a quarter of attendances to the
OL,8,FMIU were for "major" conditions
OL,9,Fincluding strokes, broken legs,
OL,10,Fappendicitis, children with acute
OL,11,Fabdominal problems, and women with
OL,12,Fpregnancy complications. The
OL,13,Fproportion was higher overnight.
OL,15,FThe acute medical assessment unit at
OL,16,Fthe hospital, which provides emergency
OL,17,Fcare for patients who, for example,
OL,18,Fhave suffered a stroke or heart
OL,19,Fattack, remains a 24-hour service at
OL,20,FPrince Philip Hospital and is not part
OL,21,Fof this temporary change.
